       	<body n="f1f0f0"><!-- Change; this is the color of the MS page; value can be any color -->
			<div rend="brown"><!-- Change; this is the color of the writing; only use auto-suggested values -->

	<pb facs="liv_020010_0001" n="0001"/><!-- Change and repeat as necessary. Always indent <pb>, as here. -->
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><space extent="6" unit="words"/><settlement>Philipton</settlement>
<lb/><space extent="6" unit="words"/><space extent="2" unit="chars"/><date when="1850-05-23">May 23 <hi rend="underline">1850</hi></date></p>
<lb/>
<lb/>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">My dear <persName>M<hi rend="sup dotted-underline">r</hi> Freeman</persName></p>
<lb/><p><space extent="2" unit="words"/><space extent="2" unit="chars"/>Owing to the detentions of
<lb/>the past by the <unclear>rains</unclear><!-- rains MBT --> and my absence <unclear>into</unclear>
<lb/><region>Caffreland</region> for the recovery of <persName>M<hi rend="sup underline">rs</hi> Read</persName>,
<lb/>and one of our <choice><sic>childrens</sic><corr>children's</corr></choice> healths I could
<lb/>not reply to yours of the 4 ultimo till now.</p> <!-- is 4 ultimo May or April 4th? HB --><!-- I'm not sure MBT -->
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">1<supplied>.</supplied> I shall take the earliest opportunity of communicating <!-- Not sure how we want to code this list? HB --><!-- I think it's ok as is. MBT -->
<lb/>with <persName>M<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> <unclear>Ulbrecht</unclear></persName> about his son.</p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">2. I have not had any recent information
<lb/>about <region><unclear><app><rdg>Madaars</rdg><rdg>Madaan</rdg></app></unclear> country</region> - however I <choice><sic>dont</sic><corr>don't</corr></choice> hear
<lb/>a word now about the <unclear>task</unclear> - On <persName>Campbell</persName>
<lb/>shaking his <unclear>tardant</unclear> over <unclear>Lin H</unclear> by the<!-- Whole line is unclear to me, to be honest! HB --><!-- There's a reference to Lin IL on page 2. maybe "shake his tardant at Lin IL by the" MBT --><!-- Gave it a shot. AW -->
<lb/>publication of <bibl>your letter</bibl> <unclear>may</unclear> for

	<pb facs="liv_020010_0002" n="0002"/>
<lb/>the present <unclear></unclear> farther proceedings &#8211;
<lb/>I met <persName>M<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> <unclear>Caldewood</unclear></persName> <date when="1850-05-22">yesterday</date> &amp; he
<lb/>told me that the <unclear><term type="collective">Boars</term></unclear> have been causing <!-- My instinct is this is Boers, but totes doesn't look like it so I am at a loss! HB --><!-- Boers is my instinct too, but agreed. Maybe also Baans? MBT --><!-- I've gone with Boars. AW -->
<lb/>a disturbance among the <unclear><term type="collective">Tambookies</term></unclear><!-- orgName? MBT -->, <add place="inline"><unclear><seg rend="small">that</seg> <add place="below">is</add></unclear></add><!-- that is? MBT -->
<lb/>they have threatened to drive <unclear>them</unclear> out
<lb/>of their country &amp; that <del><unclear><gap extent="1" unit="words"/></unclear></del><!-- length word? --> he had advised
<lb/>the <unclear><gap extent="1" unit="words"/></unclear><!-- Looks like faut? MBT --> to send a force to apprehend
<lb/>the <unclear>ringleaders</unclear> away the <unclear>Boars</unclear> - but
<lb/>that <unclear><persName>Lin H</persName></unclear> thinks from it - It is to be
<lb/><unclear>bourne</unclear><!-- bourne MBT --> in mind that <hi rend="underline"><unclear>He</unclear></hi> first promised
<lb/>the <unclear><term type="collective">Boers</term></unclear> that he would parcel out
<lb/><unclear><persName>Tamkaolund</persName></unclear><!-- I think this is the region mentioned earlier MBT --> among them - I think
<lb/><unclear><persName>Lin A</persName></unclear> spoke about it to you<supplied>.</supplied></p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">3. "<unclear>I know one</unclear><!-- I have aue? MBT --> you likely to be offended by the
<lb/>constitution <del>"</del><hi rend="sup underline"><unclear>9</unclear></hi>" If justice is done there &amp; is if
<lb/>all who have property to the amount of 50 £ <!-- The pound sign he draws has an extra line through the center - how to notate? HB -->
<lb/>be fit for <unclear><gap extent="1" unit="words"/> then will be nearly 7 or <del><gap extent="1" unit="chars"/></del><add place="over-text">8</add> as he</unclear> <!-- Again, this whole line is a bit murky for me... HB --><!-- be fit for elections then will be newly 7 or 8ao be? MBT -->

	<pb facs="liv_020010_0003" n="0003"/>
<lb/>have the right of <unclear>duking</unclear> as nearly all the
<lb/><unclear>cups</unclear> <unclear>are</unclear> valued by the <unclear><orgName>Road Board</orgName></unclear><!-- Road Board? Also organization? MBT --> at
<lb/>from 50 to 70 £ &#8211; <space extent="2" unit="chars"/>The <unclear>diamond</unclear> should
<lb/>be <unclear><gap extent="1" unit="words"/></unclear> immediately as <choice><sic>then</sic><corr>the</corr></choice> ostensible reason
<lb/>for not building good houses is for
<lb/><unclear>want</unclear><!-- I read this as want too. MBT--> of that &amp; the <add place="below">^</add> <add place="above">want of</add> security &amp; sense of security
<lb/>of life and property - The <term type="collective">Natives</term> look on
<lb/>the present peace as a hushed volcano = <add place="inline" rend="small"><unclear>therefore</unclear></add>
<lb/>they are disinclined to build at least for the
<lb/>present -</p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">4. The holder of <region>lands at <unclear>Kat River</unclear></region> may sell
<lb/>and transfer <unclear>these</unclear> lands - &amp; therefore it is very
<lb/>likely in a <unclear>shout</unclear> the lands may fall into the
<lb/>hands of others &#8212;</p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">5<supplied>.</supplied> The only thing that can put off this is that the
<lb/><orgName><term type="collective">English</term> <unclear>Prolution</unclear> Society</orgName> buy up all <hi rend="underline">vacant</hi>
<lb/><unclear>cufs.</unclear> &amp; sell them again to other industrious
<lb/><term type="collective">Natives</term> - <del type="strikethrough">This</del> There is no risk in such

	<pb facs="liv_020010_0004" n="0004"/>
<lb/>a plan. The old <orgName><term type="collective">English</term> anti-slavery</orgName> &amp;
<lb/><orgName><unclear>Prolution</unclear> Societies</orgName> must not abandon
<lb/>the <term type="collective">Natives</term> &#8212;</p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">6. I am <del type="strikethrough">not</del> of opinion that the <term type="collective">Natives</term> will
<lb/>suffer greatly from the Establishment of a
<lb/>representative <unclear>assembly</unclear> - but move from a
<lb/>federal union -</p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">7 I shall write to <persName>M<hi rend="sup">r</hi> <unclear><gap extent="1" unit="words"/></unclear></persName> by next
<lb/>post about the accounts -</p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">I <unclear>intent</unclear> this newly as an outline of my
<lb/>views - but I shall <choice><sic>write</sic><corr></corr></choice> <unclear>deliberately write</unclear> in
<lb/>the <unclear>conjunction</unclear> with my <unclear>father</unclear> &amp; drink<!-- drink mbt -->
<lb/>to the <unclear><orgName>mission Bloanfuld</orgName> thaut?</unclear> &#8212;</p> <!-- Yikes, this line! HB --><!-- mission Bloanfuld thaut? MBT --><!-- As good as guess as any. AW -->
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">Be so kind my dear <unclear><persName>Lin</persName></unclear> as to present
<lb/>my kindest reagrds to <persName>M<hi rend="sup">rs</hi> Freeman</persName>
<lb/>&amp; your excellent daughters &amp; <unclear>believe</unclear> me</p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><space extent="2" unit="words"/><space extent="2" unit="chars"/>Yours respectfully &amp; affectionately</p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><space extent="6" unit="words"/><hi rend="underline"><persName>James Read</persName></hi></p>
        
			</div>
